4 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Commissioning resolution. (1) The resolution naming the
5 commissioners must include their commission. The commission must include but is not limited to the following
6 components:
7 (a) A commissioner may not vote for or otherwise promote a change to the traditional convention
8 rule of decision on the floor and in the committee of the whole that each state has one vote.
9 (b) A commissioner may not vote in favor of a proposed amendment that would alter the text of the
10 specific guarantees of individual liberty established by the United States constitution, including the original
11 United States constitution, the bill of rights, and the 13th, 14th, 15th, 19th, 23rd, 24th, and 26th amendments.
12 (2) The commissioning resolution must clearly state the scope of the commissioners' authority,
13 which is limited by:
14 (a) (i) the subject matter enumerated in the 34 state applications that triggered the convention if
15 this state was not one of the two-thirds of the states applying for the convention; or
16 (ii) the subject matter in this state's application if this state was one of the two-thirds of the states
17 applying for the convention; and
18 (b) any additional instructions from the legislature, whether in the commissioning resolution or
19 issued subsequently.
20 (3) The legislature may provide additional instructions at any time through a subsequent
21 resolution. The clerk of the house of representatives shall provide a copy of the resolution to each
22 commissioner and to the advisory committee.
23
