9 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Vacancies. A vacancy on the commission must be filled by the advisory
10 committee's selection of an interim commissioner until a joint session of the legislature selects a permanent
11 replacement.
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Compensation and expenses. A commissioner is entitled to receive the
14 same compensation and expenses as a legislator as provided in 5-2-301.
15
16 NEW SECTION. Section 10. Emolument and gift prohibition. (1) During a commissioner's time of
17 service, the commissioner may not accept any gifts or benefits with a combined value of more than $200, other
18 than from a member of the commissioner's family and of the kind customarily granted by a member of one's
19 family.
20 (2) For the purposes of this section, the term "gift or benefit" must be construed liberally to include
21 current and future loans, lodging, food, offer of prospective employment, and other actual and prospective
22 benefits. An employer's decision to continue paying a commissioner's current salary may not be construed as a
23 gift.
